                        <summary>
                            <p>Trichy, upper cave. Inscription recording the endowment of gold for maintaining perpetual lamps.</p>
                            <p>VG: Lalitāṅkura cave temple in Trichy (Tirucirāppaḷḷi), Trichy taluk and district; at the entrance of the temple, on the flat surface before the eastern pilaster; regnal year 4 and 2501 days of Māṟañcaṭaiyaṉ; ARIE 1904, no. 414 (+ pp. 275–276); TLI Tp 1133; SII 17.444 (text not given); IEP 36 [K.G. Krishnan omitted lines 24–26].</p>
